    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-12-18T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-12-18T06:00:00-05:00" n="435"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d435">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.<gloss target="#t_BC1">BC</gloss>
                    Indonesia/12–1848: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Batavia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Livengood</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d435fn1">Repeated to Paris (for Jessup) on the same
                        day.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Batavia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-12-18T19:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 18, 1948—7 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 18—10:54 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1109. <gloss target="#t_Gocus1">Gocus</gloss> 494. Re paragraph 2 <gloss
                        target="#t_Gocus1">Gocus</gloss> 493.<note n="2" xml:id="d435fn2">Telegram
                        1108, December 18, <ref target="#pg_574">p. 574</ref>.</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss> Secretariat Batavia received telegraphically
                    from <gloss target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss> Kaliurang this afternoon following text
                    almost verbatim as drafted last night.</p>
                <p>[Here follows text of supplementary report by the <gloss target="#t_GOC1"
                        >GOC</gloss> at Kaliurang, December 18, printed in <gloss target="#t_SC1"
                        >SC</gloss>, <hi rend="italic">3rd yr., Suppl.</hi> (Dec), page 215.]</p>
                <p>“5. At special meeting of <gloss target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss> held in Kaliurang
                    at 10 a. m. on 18 December the deputy of USRep introduced above 3 documents in
                        <gloss target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss> as documents bearing on status of
                    negotiations. <gloss target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss> decided to submit documents
                    with a statement of attendant circumstances in form of a special report to
                        <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> supplementing the special report of 12
                    Dec. 1948 in order keep members of <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> currently
                    informed at critical time”.</p>
                <p>Secretariat Batavia will despatch foregoing text telegraphically to <gloss
                        target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> Paris tonight with covering message of
                    transmission. Report also being made available two parties with request any
                    comments be telegraphed direct <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>. Signed
                    Cochran.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Livengood</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
